<p>As such, the game's reported inclusion on PS Plus would give PlayStation a boost should those other formats be announced imminently.</p>
<p>It also continues momentum for the series, following the release last month of <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/silent-hill-f">Silent Hill f</a> developed by NeoBards Entertainment and published by Konami.</p>
<p>"Silent Hill f's frustrating first-half is outweighed by a brilliant, delirious second that's well worth the initial slog," reads our <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/silent-hill-f-review">Silent Hill f review</a>.</p>
<p>Bloober, meanwhile, released <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/cronos-the-new-dawn">Cronos: The New Dawn</a> last month, its original sci-fi survival horror set in 1980's Poland that's <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/cronos-the-new-dawn-review">also been well-received</a>.</p>
<p>Last week, <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/bloober-confirms-silent-hill-1-remake-in-production-and-wont-rule-out-a-cronos-sequel-just-yet">Bloober confirmed a remake of Silent Hill 1 is now in full production</a>, and hasn't ruled out a sequel to Cronos.</p>
<p>Sony already revealed the <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/here-are-our-ps-plus-monthly-and-catalogue-games-for-october">PS Plus games for October</a> at its State of Play stream, which includes <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/alan-wake-2">Alan Wake 2</a>, Cocoon, and Goat Simulator 3. Silent Hill 2 would seemingly be a welcome surprise extra.</p>



